name: Love never fails.
description:
Leah and Rick have joined forces to raise funds for the Austin Children's Shelter. 

DID YOU KNOW? In the USA, Texas has the most fatalities from child abuse and neglect, according to a study conducted by Texans Care for Children, a child-advocacy agency.

WE WANT TO HELP! Our collaborative piece, entitled "Love never fails." is a limited addition, 18" x 24" signed and numbered print. 

By purchasing this print, you make a big difference in the life of a boy or a girl, providing hope and compassion in their greatest time of need.

After printing costs, all proceeds will go to the Austin Children's Shelter! This will help provide a safe environment with nurturing staff who help children on their journey through healing, recovery, and a healthy transition back into our community.

"Love always protects, never loses faith, is always hopeful, and endures through every circumstance. Love never fails."

THANK YOU for showing your love and support!

Leah & Rick

name: This Land
description:
THIS LAND (42″ x 32″)
signed and numbered, 
limited edition print

Rick Sinnett’s latest artistic journey will be painting the side of ROCKTOWN Climbing Gym, a massive grain silo located in Downtown Oklahoma City. Right along I-40, this public art piece will measure 100′ x 128′. Entitled THIS LAND, the mural is a gift to the people of Oklahoma and all who pass through.

MAKE MOTHMAN’s VISION A REALITY! By purchase a giant limited addition THIS LAND print, you will help fund this Silo Art Project as well as show your support for local art in Oklahoma. We’ve almost reached our goal but we need your help.

Thanks to ALL who BELIEVE in the power of public art and want to help bring THIS LAND to life.

name: Phish at the Zoo
description:
PHISH AT THE ZOO (20″ x 30″)
signed and numbered,
limited edition print on canvas 

Rock band and masters of musical improve, PHISH played at the Zoo Amphitheatre in Oklahoma City recently. It was a beautiful night filled with friends and loved ones. With a full house rockin’ their socks off, the band did not disappoint and played for over 5 hours. It was an amazing show! 

This wicked psychedelic PHISH AT THE ZOO print is a perfect piece for your collection.

name: Owsley Mandala
description:
Owsley Mandala (36" x 36") signed and numbered print

Better know as BEAR, Augustus Owsley Stanley of the Grateful Dead was the inventor of THE WALL OF SOUND. This mandala was created in honor of his life.

This psychedelic radial design includes the moth, moon, fish, flowers, and eyes of the watcher. They are all in symmetrical balance in a beautiful array representing the frequencies of infinity.

name: Three Days
description:
Three Days (24" x 24") signed and numbered print
Sun, moth, and elephant in balance - This psychedelic piece depicts the reverberating sun with green eyes, and the moth centers the piece with three elephants drinking from a spring.
